headline: Micron’s Massive AI Memory Buildout Tests Multi Year Investment Thesis
summary: Micron Technology (NasdaqGS:MU) is rolling out a large global capacity buildout, including new manufacturing sites in the U.S. and Japan. The company has opened a major new facility in India as part of a wider expansion plan reportedly totaling about $200 billion. Micron's high bandwidth memory output for 2026 is already fully committed, and it is negotiating supply agreements for 2027 as AI data center demand intensifies.
